gomodel:SYNGO_4786  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: ANK3 (ankyrin-G) co-localizes with Homer1b/c at postsynaptic densities of mouse primary cortical cultured neurons. Furthermore, ankyrin-G (ANK3) 190kDa, but not 270kDa, robustly coimmunoprecipitated with Homer1b/c in PSD-enriched fractions (Fig. 2b).. Experimental description: M&M: \"Dissociated primary cortical cultured neurons were prepared from P0 C57BL/6J (The Jackson Laboratory).\"\n\nantibody:\nmouse ankyrin-G (Neuromab; N106/36)\nrabbit ankyrin-G (SantaCruz; sc-28561)\n\n\"3XHA-ankyrin-G (EX-Mm25668-M06) was purchased from GeneCopoeia. Three domain fragments of ankyrin-G (amino acids 1-807, 808-1475, 1476-1961) were amplified from 3XHA-ankyrin-G. GFP-tagged ankyrin-G was amplified from 3XHA-ankyrin-G, and subcloned into pEGFP-N2 (#6801-1; Clontech) using the Infusion ligation independent cloning kit (Clontech). The detailed information was described previously [26, 27].\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4786" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

